Preparing for Java Backend Interviews (Coforge L1 / Service-Based Companies)?

These are real interview questions — not fancy buzzwords.

Interviewers repeat them because they test fundamentals, clarity, and real-world thinking.

If you can explain why these concepts exist (not just definitions), you're already ahead of many candidates.

Core Java (Foundations Matter)

1)What is OOP and its principles?
2)Abstract class vs Interface
3)Immutable class - why & how to create?
4) == vs equals
5)hashCode () - why is it important?
6)Comparable vs Comparator
7)Aggregation vs Composition
8)final vs finally vs finalize
9)volatile keyword - where & why used?
10)sleep() vs wait() vs notify()
11)ClassLoader and its types
12)ArrayList vs LinkedList (time complexity)

